<br />
<br />NTSC artifacting is a necessity for perfecting the accuracy of NES emulation to the point where it could pass a "Turing-test" like experiment with a real NES.  It might not change the playability of anything, but I'd say that it is far more than a toy... far more important than pixel filters that are supposed to "improve" old school graphics.  I've been considering installing Windows (and I am one of those Linux zealots), just so that I can play Nestopia, which has NTSC emulation  <img src="./images/smilies/icon_confused.gif" alt=":?" title="Confused" /></div>

