			<td valign="top">
				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">When you post these huge PNGs, it's best to convert them to 256 colors without dithering. That way they don't take up hundreds of kilobytes, which is important as a POTS dial-up connection can't download more than 300 KB per minute. No, you won't lose much visible information, as you still have 10 PNG colors per ideal NES color.
<br />
<br />Examples: <ul><li><a href="http://pics.pineight.com/nes/emu_or_video1_256.png" class="postlink">Top picture: 18 KB</a> (was 72 KB) </li><li><a href="http://pics.pineight.com/nes/emu_or_video2_256.png" class="postlink">Bottom picture: 84 KB</a> (was 411 KB) </li></ul>
<br />Which leads to another obvious way to detect the emulator image: it is much smaller because it has less noise.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

